        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 6:46AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 646 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Crow Agency, or 15 miles east of Hardin, moving
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, half inch size hail, and heavy
rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip, Busby, Lame Deer, Muddy Cluster, Northern Cheyenne
Indian Reservation and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
